  ./COVERAGE.md:815:| `org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-container-default` | [1.0-alpha-7<br>- 1.0-alpha-8](metadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Plexus Container Default is the original Plexus inversion-of-control container implementation used to discover, configure, compose, and manage Plexus components. It provides component descriptors, lifecycle handling, dependency injection, configuration conversion, logging hooks, and embeddable container APIs for Java applications.</details> | [96.6% (112/116 calls)](stats/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:816:| `org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-interpolation` | [1.0<br>- 1.29](metadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-interpolation/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Plexus Interpolation is a Java utility library for resolving and substituting expression placeholders in strings from pluggable value sources such as maps, properties, objects, and environment variables. It provides interpolator implementations, recursion handling, prefix-aware lookups, and reflection-based value extraction for tools that need Maven or Plexus-style configuration interpolation.</details> | [100.0% (5/5 calls)](stats/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-interpolation/) |
