h too, especially if there's an off-by-one issue in the coverage algorithm. It feels like understanding this dynamic coverage is key, so maybe I should fully cover line 38 and assess how it interacts with class literals.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying Dynamic Coverage Issues**\\n\\nI’m grappling with the absence of line 39 and whether dynamic coverage is misleading. Is line 38 possibly affecting this? The user mentioned line 39, though covering both branches feels more natural. I’m not sure if I need a reset since the first invalid call sets a static field, and the second covers the non-null case. There’s no need for a method handle, but I'm contemplating if prior tests impact the assertions using MapOrientedComponent.class.getName at compile time.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering attempts and edits**\\n\\nThe user mentioned that we've used one attempt, which might mean we need to try again. I’m thinking about whether to use `assertAll`, but that doesn't seem right since we need to maintain a \\\"one-to-one mapping.\\\" It looks like we already have a dedicated file for that purpose. So, the plan is to go ahead and make necessary edits now to ensure everything aligns properly. Let's focus on this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_eAOJCuwmvGJzXSAOWxKdvQlR|fc_0fc67562af7f144f016a3f2fa90fec819483bdc446b21ec20f", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-11/src/test/java/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_container_default/MapOrientedComponentConfiguratorTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.MethodOrderer;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Order;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.TestMethodOrder;\n\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.util.Map;\n", "newText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.util.Map;\n"}, {"oldText": "@TestMethodOrder(MethodOrderer.OrderAnnotation.class)\npublic class MapOrientedComponentConfiguratorTest {\n    @Test\n    @Order(1)\n    public void resolvesMapOrientedComponentTypeThroughCompilerGeneratedClassLiteralHelper() throws Exception {\n        MethodHandle classLiteralHelper = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(\n            MapOrientedComponentConfigurator.class,\n            MethodHandles.lookup()\n        ).findStatic(\n            MapOrientedComponentConfigurator.class,\n            \"class$\",\n            MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class)\n        );\n\n        Class<?> resolvedType = invokeClassLiteralHelper(\n            classLiteralHelper,\n            mapOrientedComponentTypeNameSelectedAtRuntime()\n        );\n\n        assertEquals(MapOrientedComponent.class, resolvedType);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    public void rejectsComponentsThatDoNotAcceptMapConfiguration() throws Exception {\n        MapOrientedComponentConfigurator configurator = new MapOrientedComponentConfigurator();\n        Object component = nonMapOrientedComponentSelectedAtRuntime();\n\n        ComponentConfigurationException exception = assertThrows(\n            ComponentConfigurationException.class,\n            () -> configurator.configureComponent(component, new XmlPlexusConfiguration(\"configuration\"), null, null)\n        );\n\n        assertTrue(exception.getMessage().contains(\"can only process implementations\"));\n        assertTrue(exception.getMessage().contains(MapOrientedComponent.class.getName()));\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(3)\n", "newText": "public class MapOrientedComponentConfiguratorTest {\n    @Test\n    public void rejectsComponentsThatDoNotAcceptMapConfiguration() throws Exception {\n        MapOrientedComponentConfigurator configurator = new MapOrientedComponentConfigurator();\n\n        ComponentConfigurationException firstException = rejectNonMapOrientedComponent(configurator);\n        ComponentConfigurationE